  <div class="style1">
    <p>
      Rspec keeps track of many different pieces of information for each test it runs. Occasionally, it can be useful to
      print this information to the screen or use this information while the test is running. Fortunately, Rspec allows
      for this information to be accessed. In order to access the information that Rspec is holding about the current test,
      the example.metadata hash can be accessed. The example below shows how to do this.
    </p>
