    <p>
      Through adding the example variable to the block, Rspec is allowed to pass the information needed into the test when
      yielding. In the example above, all of the metadata is printed out after the test. The following image shows the output.
    </p>
    <img src="images/metadata_output.png" alt="Metadata_Output.png">
    <p>
      As the image shows, the metadata hash gives us access to information such as the file_path, line_number,
      test_description, and result of the test from within the test itself.
    </p>
